### Session Timeout Test — SC-10

**Test procedure:** Authenticate to OpenMRS test environment; leave session idle for 16 minutes; attempt to access a patient record.

**Test execution:** Assessor authenticates with test clinical account. Waits 16 minutes without interaction. Navigates to patient record. OpenMRS presents login page — session has been terminated. Assessor confirms that the session was terminated and that no patient data was accessible after the timeout.

**Verification of 2-minute warning:** Assessor authenticates again; at the 13-minute mark, a session timeout warning dialog appears offering to extend the session. Session extension confirmed working. After 15 minutes without extension, session terminates. ✓

**Result:** Session timeout implemented as documented. Finding: none.

